% Purpose: Document loader agent extracting text and structure from PDFs and other documents

% Requirements
- Create Kafka consumer agent (ingest.document_loader.v1)
- Process document artifacts (PDF, DOCX, TXT)
- Use pypdf for PDF parsing with page-level and character offset extraction
- Create EvidenceUnit records with document locators (page number, char_offset_start, char_offset_end)
- Preserve document structure (headings, lists, tables)
- Extract metadata (author, creation date)
- Handle OCR for scanned documents
- Store artifacts in MinIO

% Output Format
- Generate Python module at src/agents/document_loader.py
- Include comprehensive type hints
- Use async/await patterns

% Dependencies
- proto_schemas_Python.prompt
- kafka_consumer_base_Python.prompt
- kafka_producer_base_Python.prompt
- grpc_client_base_Python.prompt

% Implementation Notes
- Use pypdf for PDF parsing
- Use python-docx for DOCX parsing
- Implement OCR fallback
